docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON. THE new Commissioner of the Federal Food and Drug Administration, a wiry, youthful man of 43 with graying crew cut hair, sits at his oversized desk going through a stack of documents. His bushy eyebrows are bunched over deep-set eyes in intense concentration. Tne phone behind him buzzes softly and he swivels briskly to pick up the receiver. "Dr. Goddard," he answers simply.
